Introduction In my last post, I wrote about modes in Vim and how to save and quit out of Vim, but I didn&rsquo;t touch on how to move around Vim.
You might ask, &ldquo;Why would I want to learn how to move around in Vim when you can just use the mouse and arrow keys?&rdquo;
There are a couple of reasons why you shouldn&rsquo;t (or perhaps can&rsquo;t) use the mouse or arrow keys.

So, I&rsquo;ve been using Hugo to generate this blog, and I thought I would make a Makefile to compile and clean up the working directory.
